whereas.text:
Whereas 39 years ago, on March 29, 1973, the last 2,500
			 troops were withdrawn from South Vietnam thus ending military involvement in
			 what is now the longest war in United States history;

Whereas March 29, 2012, was declared Vietnam Veterans Day
			 by Presidential Proclamation with the support of Congress on the eve of the
			 50th anniversary commemoration of the beginning of the Vietnam War;

Whereas the families whose loved ones gave their lives for
			 our country during the Vietnam War, deserve the eternal gratitude and respect
			 of this Nation;
